#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn12.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: 1. Buddhavagga → abhisamayasaṃyuttaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn12.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Buddhavagga "
msgstr "1. The Buddhas "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 1. Paṭiccasamuppādasutta → desanā (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn12.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Paṭiccasamuppādasutta "
msgstr "1. Dependent Origination "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.1, sc1
msgctxt "sn12.1:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn12.1:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "sn12.1:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.1:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.1:1.7"
msgid "“paṭiccasamuppādaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you dependent origination. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:1.8"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.1:1.9"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:1.10"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn12.1:2.1"
msgid "“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, paṭiccasamuppādo? "
msgstr "“And what is dependent origination? "

msgctxt "sn12.1:2.2"
msgid "Avijjāpaccayā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā; "
msgstr "Ignorance is a condition for choices. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:2.3"
msgid "saṅkhārapaccayā viññāṇaṃ; "
msgstr "Choices are a condition for consciousness. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:2.4"
msgid "viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpaṃ; "
msgstr "Consciousness is a condition for name and form. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:2.5"
msgid "nāmarūpapaccayā saḷāyatanaṃ; "
msgstr "Name and form are conditions for the six sense fields. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:2.6"
msgid "saḷāyatanapaccayā phasso; "
msgstr "The six sense fields are conditions for contact. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:2.7"
msgid "phassapaccayā vedanā; "
msgstr "Contact is a condition for feeling. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:2.8"
msgid "vedanāpaccayā taṇhā; "
msgstr "Feeling is a condition for craving. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:2.9"
msgid "taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ; "
msgstr "Craving is a condition for grasping. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:2.10"
msgid "upādānapaccayā bhavo; "
msgstr "Grasping is a condition for continued existence. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:2.11"
msgid "bhavapaccayā jāti; "
msgstr "Continued existence is a condition for rebirth. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:2.12"
msgid "jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti. "
msgstr "Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress to come to be. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:2.13"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:2.14"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, paṭiccasamuppādo. "
msgstr "This is called dependent origination. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.2, sc3
msgctxt "sn12.1:3.1"
msgid "Avijjāya tveva asesavirāganirodhā saṅkhāranirodho; "
msgstr "When ignorance fades away and ceases with nothing left over, choices cease. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:3.2"
msgid "saṅkhāranirodhā viññāṇanirodho; "
msgstr "When choices cease, consciousness ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:3.3"
msgid "viññāṇanirodhā nāmarūpanirodho; "
msgstr "When consciousness ceases, name and form cease. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:3.4"
msgid "nāmarūpanirodhā saḷāyatananirodho; "
msgstr "When name and form cease, the six sense fields cease. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:3.5"
msgid "saḷāyatananirodhā phassanirodho; "
msgstr "When the six sense fields cease, contact ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:3.6"
msgid "phassanirodhā vedanānirodho; "
msgstr "When contact ceases, feeling ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:3.7"
msgid "vedanānirodhā taṇhānirodho; "
msgstr "When feeling ceases, craving ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:3.8"
msgid "taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodho; "
msgstr "When craving ceases, grasping ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:3.9"
msgid "upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho; "
msgstr "When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:3.10"
msgid "bhavanirodhā jātinirodho; "
msgstr "When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:3.11"
msgid "jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti. "
msgstr "When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress cease. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:3.12"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī”ti. "
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.1:3.13"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "sn12.1:3.14"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.1:3.15"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

